{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/paperfaces/go-master-portrait/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"PaperFaces portrait of a Go master","date":"2013-06-05T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"June 5th, 2013","date_from_now":"7 years ago","last_modified_at":null,"last_modified_at_from_now":null,"path":"/paperfaces/go-master-portrait/","author":null,"excerpt":"PaperFaces portrait of a Go master drawn with Paper for iOS on an iPad.","tags":["portrait","illustration","Paper for iOS"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"aspectRatio":1.3349514563106797,"src":"/static/b3164d1f656aff885091936ffa9ed128/fc20c/paperfaces-go-master.jpg","srcSet":"/static/b3164d1f656aff885091936ffa9ed128/6e883/paperfaces-go-master.jpg 275w,\n/static/b3164d1f656aff885091936ffa9ed128/a09ef/paperfaces-go-master.jpg 550w,\n/static/b3164d1f656aff885091936ffa9ed128/fc20c/paperfaces-go-master.jpg 1100w,\n/static/b3164d1f656aff885091936ffa9ed128/5d6ff/paperfaces-go-master.jpg 1650w,\n/static/b3164d1f656aff885091936ffa9ed128/d2f4e/paperfaces-go-master.jpg 2048w","sizes":"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px"},"fixed":{"src":"/static/b3164d1f656aff885091936ffa9ed128/fc20c/paperfaces-go-master.jpg","height":825,"width":1100}}},"toc":null,"comments":null,"comments_locked":null,"hide_meta":null},"id":"51d0a2ad-8a3b-5492-a313-9daee3a966a4","html":"<p><strong>Project Donator</strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/brianjolive\">@brianjolive</a> commissioned this portrait of his great friend and long time teacher of <strong>Go</strong>. Below are some in process screen captures over the course of an hour as I worked on the illustration. Let me say this, drawing straight lines on glass and getting the correct perspective isn’t easy.</p>\n<p>Laying down a base coat of watercolor using pencil to outline the game board and figure.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 1100px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.9090909090909%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"watercolor and pencil outline\"\n        title=\"watercolor and pencil outline\"\n        data-src=\"/static/31445cb3ddc94950216ca1df01f06d92/eacc7/paperfaces-go-master-process-1-lg.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/31445cb3ddc94950216ca1df01f06d92/16841/paperfaces-go-master-process-1-lg.jpg 275w,\n/static/31445cb3ddc94950216ca1df01f06d92/50c97/paperfaces-go-master-process-1-lg.jpg 550w,\n/static/31445cb3ddc94950216ca1df01f06d92/eacc7/paperfaces-go-master-process-1-lg.jpg 1100w,\n/static/31445cb3ddc94950216ca1df01f06d92/cc4ba/paperfaces-go-master-process-1-lg.jpg 1650w,\n/static/31445cb3ddc94950216ca1df01f06d92/77bd5/paperfaces-go-master-process-1-lg.jpg 2048w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>Building the foreground with layers of watercolor and pencil. I find that using lighter colors painted with 3–4 coats produces better results than one medium to dark coat.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 1100px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.9090909090909%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"Building the foreground with layers of watercolor and pencil.\"\n        title=\"Building the foreground with layers of watercolor and pencil.\"\n        data-src=\"/static/ef70ae5f1149487088872de32c7a617d/eacc7/paperfaces-go-master-process-2-lg.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/ef70ae5f1149487088872de32c7a617d/16841/paperfaces-go-master-process-2-lg.jpg 275w,\n/static/ef70ae5f1149487088872de32c7a617d/50c97/paperfaces-go-master-process-2-lg.jpg 550w,\n/static/ef70ae5f1149487088872de32c7a617d/eacc7/paperfaces-go-master-process-2-lg.jpg 1100w,\n/static/ef70ae5f1149487088872de32c7a617d/cc4ba/paperfaces-go-master-process-2-lg.jpg 1650w,\n/static/ef70ae5f1149487088872de32c7a617d/77bd5/paperfaces-go-master-process-2-lg.jpg 2048w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 1100px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.9090909090909%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"Building the foreground with layers of watercolor and pencil.\"\n        title=\"Building the foreground with layers of watercolor and pencil.\"\n        data-src=\"/static/8008fb63910c3871c91edbccc32bbd2e/eacc7/paperfaces-go-master-process-3-lg.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/8008fb63910c3871c91edbccc32bbd2e/16841/paperfaces-go-master-process-3-lg.jpg 275w,\n/static/8008fb63910c3871c91edbccc32bbd2e/50c97/paperfaces-go-master-process-3-lg.jpg 550w,\n/static/8008fb63910c3871c91edbccc32bbd2e/eacc7/paperfaces-go-master-process-3-lg.jpg 1100w,\n/static/8008fb63910c3871c91edbccc32bbd2e/cc4ba/paperfaces-go-master-process-3-lg.jpg 1650w,\n/static/8008fb63910c3871c91edbccc32bbd2e/77bd5